# PROJECT CONTEXT — EU Electrification Dashboard
# Last updated: June 2025
# Read this file at the start of every session before doing anything else.

## PROJECT GOAL
Build an EU27 country-level economic/financial dashboard.
Visualize key indicators per country, comparable across EU.
Shareable online, low cost.

## STACK
- Python 3.13
- Streamlit (dashboard UI)
- GitHub (version control + deployment trigger)
- Streamlit Community Cloud (free hosting, auto-deploys from GitHub)
- Data: CSV and Excel files (multi-country), Eurostat API (automated pulls where possible)
- Editor: Cursor (AI-native, replaces VS Code)

## PAGE STRUCTURE
1. Overview page — EU27 map + key indicators
2. 27 Country pages — identical layout, different data per country
3. Navigation/layout (Streamlit-native):
   - Left sidebar: country selector + page/section navigation
   - Main area: scrollable content
   - Optional right-side elements should be implemented via Streamlit columns/containers (no hard requirement for a separate right panel)

## DATA APPROACH
- Placeholder CSVs first (realistic but synthetic data)
- Build and test entire dashboard with placeholders
- Swap in real Eurostat data later without changing dashboard code
- CRITICAL: CSV structure must be designed carefully from day one so real data is a drop-in replacement
- Eurostat API integration planned (eurostat Python package or direct REST API)

